	"gauntlets of flaming fury (sj-dc-bst-5)" : {
		name : "Gauntlets of Flaming Fury (BST-5)",
		source : [["AL", "SJ-DC"]],
		rarity : "rare",
		description : "These gauntlets were forged from iron & meteorite by the hottest shirtless blacksmith of a fabulous ancient kingdom. After being stolen, they passed through many hands before I claimed them during the assault on the Giffstar. Any weapons I hold count as magical & I can ignite 1 or 2 held melee weapons with flames as a bonus action once per dawn. They deal +1d6 Fire until I sheathe or release either weapon. The blacksmith's screams of creation are imbued in the gauntlets, giving +2 initiative unless I'm Incapacitated.",
		descriptionFull : "During a time immemorable, and a year unknowable, the hottest blacksmith entered the most fabulous forge in a kingdom of great importance, to its citizens at least.\n   Grasping his hammer firmly, he stared deeply into the flames. Watching the curves of each tantalizing flicker, brow moist from the heat, desire began to overwhelm him.\n   Ever so gently his fingers stretched, reaching until he felt a familiar rough and cool alloy flush against his skin.\n   Ore from the sky. Ball of fire streaking across the heavens. Two shepherds nearly caught in the heat of the night. Livestock scattered. Warm glow faded in the morning light.\n   He slid the first piece of iron in, fire roaring as it received his load. In and out, in and out, thrusting deep into the forge, melding metal and heat together, the blacksmith worked into the night.\n   Ore from the earth. Veins pulsing in darkness. Arms swinging picks in rhythm. Grunting with exertion, a mass of bodies tugging and pulling to release the precious metal.\n   Up and down, his hammer swinging true. White hot alloy folding into white hot alloy. Pounding and pounding, flames licking the head with each purposeful stroke.\n   Ore of the Sky, ore of the earth, one in the forge's embrace.\n   Sparks flying, stinging against flesh, he gasped. Pain swirling with pleasure, the force of the furnace slamming against him as a pair of gauntlets began to take shape.\n   Pressing on, red glow creeping up the shaft of his hammer, his calloused hands perspiring as the heat drew ever closer. The malleability of metal, the malleability of man; was he shaping the gauntlets, or was the gauntlet shaping him?\n   Sweat and steam; hands and hammer; ingots and iron; surrendering to the forge, screaming to the rhythm of the craft, he pushed the masterpiece to completion.\n   In the morning, bare chest dripping, he collapsed, finished. Waking up a few days later, the gauntlets were missing, vanished without a trace.\n   Taken by a nameless ne'er-do-well, the cowardly thief themselves was lost history when a rock fell from the sky, crushing them.\n   Maybe the rock was really a spelljamming ship. The next record of the gauntlets has them being tossed into a chest by a pair of distracted deckhands who'd snuck away for some recreation.\n   The gauntlets slammed around inside the chest in the hold of a hammerhead ship for years before the ship was rammed by space dwarves, who used it for a monstrous plot. The attackers blasted their way into the hold and pounded the chest open.\n   One of the space dwarves grabbed the gauntlets roughly, later coming together with a tiefling dragon chosen. The gauntlets were taken in the early morning over a game of cards.\n   Tying the knot up in this story, the gauntlets were claimed in the Assault on the Giffstar to protect Bestspace from the evil alliance of Godfried and Nicolli.\n   The blacksmith's screams of creation are imbued in these gauntlets, granting the guardian property.\n   " + toUni("Guardian") + ". The item warns you, granting a +2 bonus to your Initiative rolls if you don't have the Incapacitated condition.\n   While you wear both of these steel gauntlets, any non- magical weapon you grasp with either gauntlet is treated as a magic weapon. As a bonus action, you can use the gauntlets to cause magical flames to envelop one or two melee weapons in your grasp. Each flaming weapon deals an extra 1d6 fire damage on a hit. The flames last until you sheath or let go of either weapon. Once used, this property can't be used again until the next dawn.",
		attunement : true,
		limfeaname : "Gauntlets of Flaming Fury",
		usages : 1,
		recovery : "dawn",
		action : [["bonus action", ""]],
		addMod : { type : "skill", field : "Init", mod : 2, text : "+2 bonus on Initiative rolls." },
		calcChanges: gauntletsOfFlamingFury.calcChanges,
	},
