		description : "This acrid smelling stained spellbook starts with 6 spells \u0026 is a Wizard spellcasting focus when held. The spine of a small mammal is embedded in its binding \u0026 its cover is set with a pair of perfectly preserved bead-like eyes. The book has 3 charges, 1d3 regained at dawn. With 1 charge \u0026 1 min, I can change a prepared spell to a Transmutation spell within. As an action, touch unattended nonmagical object (1 charge is 1 ft sq. +2 ft per extra charge) & turn it to another (Same or less GP value).",
