	"talking doll: grim (ccc-des-2-1)" : {
		name : "Grim, Talking Doll (CCC-DES-2-1)",
		source : [["AL","CCC"]],
		attunement : true,
		description : "This wood and fabric doll is a handsome man with ebony skin, six-fingered hands, and a rakish grin. Sometimes it moves when no one is looking or says phrases of its own with a seductive malice. During a short rest, I can teach it 6 phrases, up to 6 words each, and set observable conditions as triggers. They must happen within 5 ft. Any learned phrases are lost when I unattune.",
		descriptionFull : "This wood and fabric doll resembles a handsome man with ebony skin and curiously six-fingered hands. Its mouth sports a rakish grin. At times, the doll moves while nobody is watching, and it at times will say phrases of its own that hold a seductive malice. For example, whenever someone picks up the doll, it might say, \"Your eyes will run from blood.\"\n   While this doll is within 5 feet of you, you can spend a Short Rest telling it to say up to six phrases, none of which can be more than six words long, and set a condition under which the doll speaks each phrase. You can also replace old phrases with new ones. Whatever the condition, it must occur within 5 feet of the doll to make it speak. For example, whenever someone picks up the doll, it might say, \"I want a piece of candy.\" The doll's phrases are lost when your Attunement to the doll ends."
	},
	"talking doll: chass the unfortunate (ccc-pipyaps-dh1)" : {
		name : "Chass the Unfortunate (Talking Doll)",
		source : [["AL","CCC"]],
		attunement : true,
		description : "This doll is the remnant of Chass, an incubus in Graz'zt's service. He failed his master too many times and now lives out eternity as a toy. During a short rest, I can teach it 6 phrases, up to 6 words each, and set observable conditions as triggers. They must happen in 5 ft. I pick the words but Chass picks the intonation and attitude. Learned phrases are lost when I unattune.",
		descriptionFull : "This doll is the last remnants of a Chass, an incubus in the service of Graz'zt. He failed his master too many times and now must live out eternity as a plaything. While you do get to pick the words the doll can speak as normal, Chass gets to pick the intonation and attitude of the phrase when spoken.\n   While this doll is within 5 feet of you, you can spend a Short Rest telling it to say up to six phrases, none of which can be more than six words long, and set a condition under which the doll speaks each phrase. You can also replace old phrases with new ones. Whatever the condition, it must occur within 5 feet of the doll to make it speak. For example, whenever someone picks up the doll, it might say, \"I want a piece of candy.\" The doll's phrases are lost when your Attunement to the doll ends."
	},
	"talking doll (ccc-sea-1-1)" : {
		name : "Talking Doll (CCC-SEA-1-1)",
		source : [["AL","CCC"]],
		attunement : true,
		description : "This stuffed doll of a princely triton is a little chewed on. During a short rest, I can teach it 6 phrases, up to 6 words each, & set observable conditions in 5 ft as triggers. When found, the doll says \"I am Captain Prince Glip Glop of the Respectable House of Glop, 3rd of his Name, & Ambassador to the Material Plane!\" when asked \"What is your name?\" Phrases are lost when I unattune.",
		descriptionFull : "This stuffed doll of a princely triton looks a little chewed upon, but is otherwise none the worse for wear. When found, the doll repeats the phrase \"I am Captain Prince Glip Glop of the Respectable House of Glop, Third of his Name, and Ambassador to the Material Plane!\" when someone within 5 feet of the dolls says, \"What is your name?\"\n   While this doll is within 5 feet of you, you can spend a Short Rest telling it to say up to six phrases, none of which can be more than six words long, and set a condition under which the doll speaks each phrase. You can also replace old phrases with new ones. Whatever the condition, it must occur within 5 feet of the doll to make it speak. For example, whenever someone picks up the doll, it might say, \"I want a piece of candy.\" The doll's phrases are lost when your Attunement to the doll ends."
	},
	"talking doll: singing (ps-dc-sb-bish1)" : {
		name : "Singing Doll (Talking, SB-BISH1)",
		source : [["AL","PS-DC"]],
		attunement : true,
		description : "A weathered porcelain doll with a tattered velvet dress and painted glass eyes that follow me. It occasionally whispers fragments of nursery rhymes, lullabies, or eerie warnings in a childs voice. It's said to house the spirit of Lillia, a child once offered as a tithe to an archfey known as the Mourning Crone. During a rest, I can teach it 6 phrases, up to 6 words each, and set an observable condition to trigger each. Conditions must happen in 5 ft. Learned phrases are lost when my attunement ends.",
		descriptionLong : "A weathered porcelain doll with a tattered velvet dress and painted glass eyes that seem to follow me. When held, the doll occasionally whispers fragments of nursery rhymes, lullabies, or eerie warnings in a childs voice. It's said to house the spirit of Lillia, a child once offered as a tithe to an archfey known as The Mourning Crone. During a short rest, I can teach it 6 phrases, up to 6 words each, and set an observable condition to trigger each phrase. Conditions must happen within 5 ft. Learned phrases are lost when my attunement ends.",
		descriptionFull : "A weathered porcelain doll, no more than 18 inches tall, wears a tattered velvet dress and has painted glass eyes that seem to follow anyone who looks at it. When held, the doll occasionally whispers fragments of nursery rhymes, lullabies, or eerie warnings in a childs voice.\n   The doll is said to house the lingering spirit of Lillia, a child once offered as a tithe to an archfey known as The Mourning Crone. Instead of death, Lillia was bound to the doll, her spirit fractured across countless replicas spread throughout the realms as part of the Crones endless sorrow.\n   " + toUni("Songcraft") + ". Whenever this item is struck or is used to strike a foe, you hear a hags laughter or a whimsical song.\n   While this doll is within 5 feet of you, you can spend a Short Rest telling it to say up to six phrases, none of which can be more than six words long, and set a condition under which the doll speaks each phrase. You can also replace old phrases with new ones. Whatever the condition, it must occur within 5 feet of the doll to make it speak. For example, whenever someone picks up the doll, it might say, \"I want a piece of candy.\" The doll's phrases are lost when your Attunement to the doll ends.",
	},
