		source : [["AL","WBW-DC"]],
		attunement : true,
		description : "This gingham doll is shaped like a rabbit with long soft ears & a button for a nose. It smells like sulfur & its mouth is stitched in neither a smile nor frown. The eyes are black glass & stare blankly. During a short rest, I can teach it 6 phrases, up to 6 words each, and set observable conditions as triggers. They must occur in 5 ft. Phrases are lost when I unattune.",
		descriptionFull : "This gingham doll is shaped like a rabbit with long soft ears and a button for a nose. Its mouth is stitched straight in not quite a smile and not quite a frown. The eyes are black glass and stare expressionlessly.\n   " + toUni("Reek") + ". The item consistently smells like sulfur. Nothing the bearer can do, including magically, will ever get rid of the stench.\n   While this doll is within 5 feet of you, you can spend a Short Rest telling it to say up to six phrases, none of which can be more than six words long, and set a condition under which the doll speaks each phrase. You can also replace old phrases with new ones. Whatever the condition, it must occur within 5 feet of the doll to make it speak. For example, whenever someone picks up the doll, it might say, \"I want a piece of candy.\" The doll's phrases are lost when your Attunement to the doll ends."
