		description : "This spider-shaped mithral helm belonged to the drow mage Axcelia Axcelon. If held to my head, 8 thin spidery legs wrap around my face. The legs are soft & silken, both comfortable & unsettling. A worshiper of Lolth feels envy & awe at the craftsmanship. This helm has 3 charges, 1d3 regained at dawn. Use 1 charge to cast Teleport; those teleported hear \"Across the weave\" in Undercommon.",
		descriptionLong : "This mithral helm is shaped like a spider and belonged to the drow mage Axcelia Axcelon. When held to the back of my head, 8 thin spidery legs extend and wrap around my face. The legs are soft and silken, both comfortable and extremely unsettling. A worshiper of Lolth feels envy and awe at the fine craftsmanship. This helm has 3 charges, 1d3 regained at dawn. I can use 1 charge to cast Teleport from it; those teleported hear \"Across the weave\" whispered in Undercommon.",
