		name : "Luthik's Call, Silver Horn of Valhalla (MAYDAYS2-1)",
		source : [["AL","CCC"]],
		rarity : "rare",
		description : "This hollow giant eland horn has silver filigree that glimmers in moonlight. It's a holy relic, given to the faithful for brave deeds. Followers of Luthik revere those who bear it in battle and tales of my heroic deeds are etched on its surface in Orcish. It lets me speak Orc and resists being used by anyone else. As a Magic action once per 7 days, I can blow the horn to summon 2 spirits in 60 ft. These Berserkers can't be Charmed or Frightened, disappear after 1 hr or at 0 HP, are Friendly and obey my orders.",
		descriptionLong : "Luthik's Call is a holy relic, given to the faithful for the bravest deeds. The hollowed giant eland horn has silver filigree that glimmers in moonlight. It lets me speak Orc and resists being used by anyone else. Followers of Luthik revere those who bear the horn in battle and tales of my heroic deeds are etched on its surface in Orcish. As a Magic action once per 7 days, I can blow the horn to summon 2 warrior spirits from Ysgard in 60 ft. These Berserkers are immune to Charmed and Frightened, disappear after 1 hr or at 0 HP, are Friendly and obey my commands.",
		descriptionFull : "This item is a blessed holy relic, granted to the faithful of Luthik for only the most valorous of deeds. Luthik's Call is made from a hollowed giant eland horn, adorned with silver filigree that glimmers in moonlight. Tales of the wielder's mettle are etched upon its surface in orcish, chronicling for all to read the heroic deeds of its owner. Followers of Luthik will revere those who bear this item in battle. Enemies of the Den Mother may try to steal it away but will be disappointed, as Luthik's Call resists use by any person except the one to whom it was gifted.\n    The horn's owner can speak and understand the orc language while Luthik's Call is on their person.\n    You can take a Magic action to blow this horn. In response, warrior spirits from the plane of Ysgard appear in unoccupied spaces within 60 feet of you. Each spirit uses the Berserker stat block and returns to Ysgard after 1 hour or when it drops to 0 Hit Points. The spirits look like living breathing warriors, and they have Immunity to the Charmed and Frightened conditions. Once you use the horn, it can't be used again until 7 days have passed.\n    The silver horn summons 2 Berserkers. They are Friendly to you and your allies and follow your commands.",
