		descriptionLong : "This lyre is made of pulverized bone, glowing embers of cremated flesh, and the final exhale of a nalfeshnee slain on Belistor, the 277th layer of the Abyss. While shaped like a lyre, the bone, and embers swirl on containing winds. As I gesture to play, they form into strings. If the lyre is played without attuning, DC 15 Wis save or take 2d4 Psychic dmg. I can play the lyre to cast 1 of its spells: Fly, Invisibility, Levitate, and Protection from Evil and Good, Stone Shape, Wall of Fire, and Wind Wall. Each can be cast once per dawn using my spell ability and save DC.",
