		description : "This elegant lute is made of rare Feywild wood and lets me speak Sylvan. It glows when played, with shadows dancing and ghostly Sylvan voices singing. If Fey are in 120 ft, it sheds 10-ft of dim light. If played unattuned, DC 15 Wis save or 2d4 Psychic. I can play it to cast 1 of 7 spells (each once per dawn) with my spell ability and save DC.",
		descriptionLong : "This elegant lute is made of rare Feywild wood. It glows when played, shadows dancing across nearby surfaces and ghostly voices singing in Sylvan. The lute also glows warmly when Fey are within 120 ft, shedding 10-ft of dim light and making the shadows cavort again. I can speak Sylvan when attuned. If played without attuning, DC 15 Wis save or 2d4 Psychic damage. I can play the lute to cast 1 of 7 spells: Fly, Invisibility, Levitate, Protection from Evil and Good, Animal Friendship, Protection from Energy (Fire only), and Protection from Poison. Each can be cast once per dawn using my spellcasting ability and spell save DC.",	
