		description : "The Librarian gave me this tome of stories, poems and songs from Berdusk, home to the Bardic College of Doss. I can perform work aloud to cast 1 of 7 spells (once per dawn each) with my spellcasting ability and DC. If perform unattuned, DC 15 Wis save or 2d4 Psychic. As Magic action, my voice carries up to 600 ft until my next turn ends.",
		descriptionLong : "The Librarian has gifted me a copy of this tome, which contains some of the best pieces of writing published in Berdusk, home to the Bardic College of Doss. Among the collected stories, poems, and songs are ones that can be performed aloud to cast 1 of its spells: Fly, Invisibility, Levitate, Protection from Evil and Good, Animal Friendship, Protection from Energy (Fire only), and Protection from Poison. Each can be cast once per dawn using my spellcasting ability and save DC. If performed without attuning, DC 15 Wis save or take 2d4 Psychic dmg. I can also use a Magic action to cause my voice to carry clearly for up to 600 ft until my next turn ends.",
		descriptionFull : "The Librarian has gifted you a copy of this tome, which contains some of the best pieces of writing published in Berdusk, home to the Bardic College of Doss. Among the collected stories, poems and songs are ones that can be performed (read out loud) to cast the item's spells.\n   " + toUni("War Leader") + ". You can take a Magic action to cause your voice or signal to carry clearly for up to 600 feet until the end of your next turn.\n   An Instrument of the Bards is superior to an ordinary instrument in every way. Seven types of these instruments exist, each named after a bard college. The Instruments of the Bards table lists the spells common to all instruments, as well as the spells specific to each one and its rarity. A creature that attempts to play the instrument without being attuned to it must succeed on a DC 15 Wisdom saving throw or take 2d4 Psychic damage.\n   You can play the instrument to cast one of its spells. Once the instrument has been used to cast a spell, it can't be used to cast that spell again until the next dawn. The spells use your spellcasting ability and spell save DC.\n   All instruments of the bards can be used to cast the following spells: Fly, Invisibility, Levitate, and Protection from Evil and Good.\n   In addition, the Doss lute can be used to cast Animal Friendship, Protection from Energy (fire only), and Protection from Poison.",
