		name : "Communicator Model Berlo 2.0 (Instrument of Scribing)",
		source : [["AL","SJ-DC"]],
		rarity : "common",
		description : "This simple semi-circular disk turns into an armbrace around my dominant forearm, with buttons for a multitude of  functions. I can illusorily alter its appearance in minor ways. It has 3 charges, regained at dawn. Play as Magic action and use 1 charge to write magical message up to 6 words in known language on visible mundane object or surface in 30 ft. Bards can scribe up to 13 words and make the message glow faintly. It fades in 24 hrs or when dispelled.",
		descriptionFull : "Appearing as a simple semi-circular disk, the Communicator will transform, expanding its parts until it because an armbrace around the bearer's dominant forearm, buttons showing on it for a multitude of functions.\n   " + toUni("Illusion") + ". The item is imbued with illusion magic, allowing its bearer to alter the item's appearance in minor ways. Such alterations don't change how the item is worn, carried, or wielded, and they have no effect on its other magical properties.\n   This musical instrument has 3 charges and regains all expended charges daily at dawn. While you are playing it, you can take a Magic action to expend 1 charge and write a magical message on a nonmagical object or surface that you can see within 30 feet of yourself. The message can be up to six words long and is written in a language you know. If you are a Bard, you can scribe an additional seven words and make the message glow faintly, allowing it to be seen in nonmagical Darkness. Casting the Dispel Magic spell on the message erases it. Otherwise, the message fades away after 24 hours.",
