		descriptionFull : "At the center of a gaudy copper setting rests a small, tearshaped geode, 1\" wide and 2\" tall. The crystals are blood red and metallic gold, and they shimmer when exposed to even a small amount of light. If a chain originally accompanied this bauble, it is long gone. The periapt is now hung from a cord of coarse braided hair, possibly from a horse or donkey.\n   While wearing this pendant, you can take a Magic action to regain 2d4 + 2 Hit Points. Once used, this property can't be used again until the next dawn.\n   In addition, you have Advantage on saving throws to avoid or end the Poisoned condition while you wear this pendant.",
