		rarity : "uncommon",
		description : "A weathered lantern forged from cold iron and darkened silver, handle wrapped in aged leather that carries the faint scent of burnt sage. The interior is etched with ancient wards to repel the influence of dark creatures. When ignited, the flame burns a ghostly blue-green. It lasts for 6 hrs on 1 pint of oil, shedding 30-ft of bright light & 30-ft more dim. Invisible objects & creatures are visible in the bright light. Lower the hood with Utilize action for 5-ft dim light. While underground, I always know my depth & the direction to the nearest upward path.",
		descriptionLong : "A weathered lantern forged from cold iron and darkened silver, handle wrapped in aged leather that carries the faint scent of burnt sage. The interior is etched with ancient wards to repel the influence of dark creatures it was made to hunt. When ignited, the flame burns a ghostly blue-green, unsettling to those who traffic in curses and nightmares  Crafted by exorcists and hag-hunters of old, these l anterns were once essential tools of the ORDOs Diabolous and Hereticus specs. Most were lost to time, shattered by their owners or stolen by the very creatures they were meant to repel. It burns for 6 hrs on 1 pint of oil, shedding 30-ft of bright light & 30-ft more dim. Invisible objects & creatures are visible in the bright light. If I lower the hood with a Utilize action, it sheds 5-ft dim light. While underground, I always know my depth & the direction to the nearest upward path.",
		descriptionFull : "A weathered lantern forged from cold iron and darkened silver, its handle wrapped in aged leather that carries the faint scent of burnt sage. The interior is etched with ancient wards, repelling the influence of the dark creatures it was made to hunt. When ignited, the lanterns flame burns a ghostly blue-green, unsettling to those who traffic in curses and nightmares.\n   Crafted by exorcists and hag-hunters of old, Witchward Lanterns were once essential tools of the ORDOs Diabolous and Hereticus specs. Most were lost to time, shattered by their owners or stolen by the very creatures they were meant to repel. The discovery of one still functional suggests the party is treading in the footsteps of an older, unfinished hunt.Light like this dont come from mercyit comes from those who bled before me, and I thank every ghost it keeps at bay.-Agent Bloodbeard\n   " + toUni("Delver") + ". While underground, you always know the items depth below the surface and the direction to the nearest staircase, ramp, or other path leading upward.\n   While lit, this hooded lantern burns for 6 hours on 1 pint of oil, shedding Bright Light in a 30-foot radius and Dim Light for an additional 30 feet. Invisible creatures and objects are visible as long as they are in the lantern's Bright Light. You can take a Utilize action to lower the hood, reducing the lantern's light to Dim Light in a 5-foot radius.",
