	"gem of seeing: cauldron shard (ps-dc-sb-bish1)" : { // contains contributions by Larry Hoy
		name : "Cauldron Shard (Gem of Seeing, SB-BISH1)",
		source : [["AL","PS-DC"]],
		rarity : "rare",
		description : "A jagged fragment of blackened iron, still faintly warm, etched with scars from being violently sundered. The shard pulses with residual magic, a remnant of Morwen Bishop's infernal cauldron. When held to the ear, I hear whispers of old curses, spoken in a voice both distant and too close for comfort. The Bishop Covens cauldrons are legendary among hags. It has 3 charges. As a Magic action, I can use 1 charge. For 10 min, I gain 120 ft of Truesight when I peer through the shard. It regains 1d3 charges at dawn.",
		descriptionLong : "A jagged fragment of blackened iron, still faintly warm, etched with scars where it was violently sundered. The shard pulses with residual magic, a remnant of the infernal cauldron that once amplified the dark power of Morwen Bishop. When held to the ear, I hear whispers of old curses, spoken in a voice both distant and too close for comfort. The Bishop Covens cauldrons are legendary among hags, not just as tools of power, but as anchors to their malevolent spells. Some say that a reforged Bishop Cauldron could serve as a vessel to resurrect its last owner, while others whisper that such artifacts act as beacons for other hags. Even shattered, the shard remains hot, as if the cauldrons hatred still smolders within. It has 3 charges. As a Magic action, I can use 1 charge. For 10 min, I gain 120 ft of Truesight when I peer through the shard. It regains 1d3 charges at dawn.",
		descriptionFull : "A jagged fragment of blackened iron, still faintly warm to the touch, etched with runic scars where it was violently sundered. The shard pulses with residual magic, a remnant of the infernal cauldron that once amplified the dark power of Morwen Bishop. When held to the ear, one might hear whispers of old curses, spoken in a voice both distant and too close for comfort.\n   " + toUni("Strange Material") + ". The shards twisted metal and cursed origins make it an unnatural conduit.\n   The Bishop Covens cauldrons are legendary among hag-kind, not just as tools of power, but as anchors to their malevolent spells. This fragment, though broken, still carries a sliver of Morwens essenceand perhaps the attention of something far worse.\n   Some say that a reforged Bishop Cauldron could serve as a vessel to resurrect its last owner, while others whisper that such artifacts act as beacons for other hags, who will seek to reclaim what was lost.\n   Even shattered, the shard remains hotas if the cauldrons hatred still smolders within, you can feel it peering, refusing to die with its vessel.\n   This gem has 3 charges. As a Magic action, you can expend 1 charge. For the next 10 minutes, you have Truesight out to 120 feet when you peer through the gem.\n   The gem regains 1d3 expended charges daily at dawn.",
		attunement : true,
		weight : 1,
		limfeaname : "Gem of Seeing",
		usages : 3,
		recovery : "dawn",
		additional : "1d3 Recharge",
		action : [["action", "Gem of Seeing (Truesight)"]],
	},
