		source : [["AL","PO"]],
		rarity : "rare",
		description : "This ring is a single piece of mystical green glass stronger than steel. It's etched with protective runes & shimmers with an iridescent sheen. The ring is wrapped with red thread in a cluster of elegant loops that appear like lustrous gems at first glance. When worn, I gain +1 to AC and saves. I also get +4 to saves and checks made to avoid dropping or being disarmed of anything in that hand.",
		descriptionLong : "This ring is made from a single piece of mystical green glass thats stronger than steel. It's etched with protective runes and shimmers with an iridescent sheen in any light. A red thread is wrapped around the ring in a cluster of elegant loops, so lustrous that it can be mistaken for a gemstone at first glance. When worn, I gain +1 to AC and saves. I also gain +4 to saves and checks made to avoid dropping or being disarmed of any item held in that hand.",
		descriptionFull : "This green glass ring is etched with protective runes and shimmers with an iridescent sheen, even in dim light. A red thread is wrapped around it in a cluster of elegant loops, so lustrous that it could be mistaken for a gemstone at first glance.\n   The ring is made from a single piece of mystical green glass thats stronger than steel. It has the added property of making the wearer less likely to drop or lose anything held in the hand the ring is on. The wearer receives a +4 bonus to saving throws or checks made to avoid dropping or being disarmed of any item held in that hand.\n   You gain a +1 bonus to Armor Class and saving throws while wearing this ring. [Premiere version, may change]",
