		attunement : true,
		prerequisite : "Requires attunement by a spellcaster",
		prereqeval : function(v) { return v.isSpellcaster; },
		description : "This black iron rod is warm to the touch. Affixed atop is the broken horn of a balor I recognize from the past. It heightens the urge to act in selfish or malevolent ways, which explains why D'Alva was so hellbent on destroying Mogdol. The rod can be used as an arcane focus and gives resistance to Fire and Necrotic. Once per dawn, I can use it to cast Hellish Rebuke at 4th-lvl (DC 16). When I cast a spell that deals Fire or Necrotic, I can maximize the damage instead of rolling once per dawn.",
		descriptionLong : "This black iron rod is warm to the touch despite being removed from Mogdol's possession. Affixed atop is the broken horn of a balor I recognize from a past encounter. It heightens the urge to act in selfish or malevolent ways when given the chance. That at least explains why D'Alva was so hellbent on destroying Mogdol. The rod can be used as an arcane focus. It grants resistance to Fire and Necrotic dmg, and can be attuned to in 1 min. Once per dawn, I can use it to cast Hellish Rebuke as a 4th-lvl spell (save DC 16). When I cast a spell that deals Fire or Necrotic damage, I can maximize the damage instead of rolling once per dawn.",
